message: Feds move to dismiss Jeffrey Epstein's sex-trafficking indictment but officials say they have no plans to end the probe into Epstein's alleged victims' claims, and authorities are still considering charging others accused in the alleged underage sex ring.

data.description: Federal prosecutors on Monday moved to dismiss the sex trafficking indictment against Jeffrey Epstein following his suicide in federal lockup earlier this month — but officials say they have no plans to end the probe into Epstein's alleged victims' claims, and authorities are still considering cha...
data.title: Feds move to dismiss Jeffrey Epstein's sex-trafficking indictment
